ured goods. In other words, primary products, which are the main export items of lower-income countries of the region, benefited less from dynamism in regional trade than from S-S trade in general. These countries\u2019 trade in primary products was sluggish, both with China and with the ESSEA as a whole. 18 Table 4: Matrix of South-South trade in manufactured goods, 1995 and 2005 Destination ESSEA China ESSEA (excl. China) South (incl.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "18d47dd9-d57f-4a95-9b24-d31c7a6f89e8": {"__data__": {"id_": "18d47dd9-d57f-4a95-9b24-d31c7a6f89e8", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/south-south-regionalism-and-trade-cooperation-asia-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "South-South Regionalism and Trade Cooperation in the Asia-Pacific Region", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/south-south-regionalism-and-trade-cooperation-asia-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "3a725db854fb54a4c53cbcc19b63549d93b8635f623b2f8b2c5751765345f00d"}, "2": {"node_id": "13764e27-fc72-4edd-ba54-5f82484b09fa", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/south-south-regionalism-and-trade-cooperation-asia-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "50a8872b379c9982e0ea8916519f8c77848ba6303b1bfc582267f21559643c69"}}, "hash": "6c4060f87b46c3c0ea202497a